<p><b>Acronis True Image</b> is a <a href="/wiki/Disk_image" title="Disk image">disk imaging</a> and disaster recovery <a href="/wiki/Application_software" title="Application software">application</a> for computers, produced by <a href="/wiki/Acronis" title="Acronis">Acronis</a>. True Image can create an <a href="/wiki/Disk_image" title="Disk image">image</a> of a disk while it is running <a href="/wiki/Microsoft_Windows" title="Microsoft Windows">Microsoft Windows</a> or <a href="/wiki/Linux" title="Linux">Linux</a>, or offline by booting from <a href="/wiki/CD" title="CD" class="mw-redirect">CD</a>/<a href="/wiki/DVD" title="DVD">DVD</a>, <a href="/wiki/USB_flash_drive" title="USB flash drive">USB flash drives</a>, <a href="/wiki/Preboot_Execution_Environment" title="Preboot Execution Environment">PXE</a>, or other <a href="/wiki/Bootable" title="Bootable" class="mw-redirect">bootable</a> media. As a disk imaging solution, True Image can restore the previously captured image to another disk, effectively replicating the structure and contents to the new disk, also allowing partition resizing if the new disk is of different capacity.</p>
